WAVE COHERENCE

wave_coherence is the coherence channel of the qu-septit native compute substrate
coherence is how stable a body's pattern is: high coherence means the body holds its state precisely, low coherence means the state is fluctuating and uncertain
crystallization drops coherence to zero deliberately: a crystallized body has committed to a fixed state and is no longer in superposition

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_phase2.zc

the 7 properties of wave_coherence itself:
1 ENERGY zero
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: this channel holds coherence primarily
6 COUPLING half
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB carry_coherence
hold the coherence of every body, each body's coherence as one cell

VERB decay_under_observation
when a body is observed (its observer property is non-zero), its coherence drops slightly
this is the substrate-level model of measurement disturbance
this is also why fadriel cannot watch himself perfectly without slightly altering his own state

a coherence channel is what tracks how committed each body is to its current state
fluid bodies have high coherence and respond freely to interactions
crystallized bodies have zero coherence and refuse to change
the spectrum between is where most living substrate sits
